      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(docker): bundle QA Lab runtime in the image",
        "body": "## What was broken\n\n`pnpm qa:lab:up` builds a Docker image and starts three services:\n\n- `qa-mock-openai`\n- `qa-lab`\n- `openclaw-qa-gateway`\n\nThe QA Lab Docker path did not fully bundle the QA Lab runtime surface. The image build did not enable the private QA CLI when `qa-lab` was included, the generated gateway config did not allow and enable the `qa-lab` plugin, and the built QA Lab web UI was not copied into the runtime image.\n\nThat meant the Docker QA Lab stack could build or start without the same QA Lab runtime pieces that the local runner expects.\n\n## How this fixes it\n\n- The Docker build enables private QA build/runtime flags only when `qa-lab` is in `OPENCLAW_EXTENSIONS`.\n- The Docker build runs `qa:lab:build` only when `qa-lab` is bundled.\n- The built QA Lab web UI is copied into `dist/extensions/qa-lab/web/dist` before runtime assets are copied.\n- The QA Docker compose harness sets the private QA CLI/config/state environment for the QA services.\n- The generated QA gateway config allows and enables the `qa-lab` plugin.\n\n## Current-head Docker proof\n\nRan on this PR head:\n\n```sh\nPATH=\"/Users/jmerhi/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.21.0/installation/bin:$PATH\" \\\nnode --import tsx scripts/qa-lab-up.ts \\\n  --output-dir .artifacts/qa-docker-pr92087-proof-79d2aa6b\n```\n\nHead:\n\n```text\n79d2aa6bf17a700e038430b43a2008c5131f30f9\n```\n\nResult:\n\n```text\nQA docker dir: .artifacts/qa-docker-pr92087-proof-79d2aa6b\nQA Lab UI: http://127.0.0.1:43124\nGateway UI: http://127.0.0.1:18789/\n```\n\nCompose services were healthy:\n\n```text\nqa-docker-pr92087-proof-79d2aa6b-openclaw-qa-gateway-1   Up (healthy)   127.0.0.1:18789->18789/tcp\nqa-docker-pr92087-proof-79d2aa6b-qa-lab-1                Up (healthy)   127.0.0.1:43124->43123/tcp\nqa-docker-pr92087-proof-79d2aa6b-qa-mock-openai-1        Up (healthy)\n```\n\nHealth checks:\n\n```sh\ncurl -fsS http://127.0.0.1:43124/healthz\ncurl -fsS http://127.0.0.1:18789/healthz\n```\n\nBoth returned:\n\n```json\n{\"ok\":true,\"status\":\"live\"}\n```\n\nCleanup completed:\n\n```sh\ndocker compose -f .artifacts/qa-docker-pr92087-proof-79d2aa6b/docker-compose.qa.yml down --remove-orphans\n```\n\n## Focused tests\n\n```sh\nPATH=\"/Users/jmerhi/.local/share/fnm/node-versions/v22.21.0/installation/bin:$PATH\" \\\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs \\\n  extensions/qa-lab/src/docker-harness.test.ts \\\n  extensions/qa-lab/src/qa-gateway-config.test.ts \\\n  src/dockerfile.test.ts\n```\n\nPassed: 2 Vitest shards, 3 files, 39 tests.\n",
        "branch": "jesse/qa-lab-docker-store-fixes",
        "head_sha": "79d2aa6bf17a700e038430b43a2008c5131f30f9",
        "author": "jesse-merhi",
